# [`dput()`]{.blue}
 
 
### [dput]{.blue}(*thingy*){.center} 
 
# What it does 

+ Print a text version of *any* object in the console (by default).
  
 
# Demo code 

```{r, comment=""}
dput(names(iris))
```
  
 
# Usefull stuff 

+ It is very convenient if you want to get a set of variable names for later processing.
